1
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:40,950
[Shadow Love]

2
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,950
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:03,450
[Ninglan]

4
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,700
We've been walking all day.

5
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:09,700
Why don't we stay here for the night?

6
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:10,580
Alright.

7
00:02:12,430 --> 00:02:13,360
Watch the steps.

8
00:02:14,229 --> 00:02:14,890
Be careful.

9
00:02:15,230 --> 00:02:15,870
Take care.

10
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,130
[Luming House]

11
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:18,760
Sir, Ma'am, are you here for a room?

12
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:19,480
Do you have any rooms available?

13
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,950
Sir, you're in luck.

14
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:21,790
There's still

15
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:23,080
one superior room left.

16
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:23,520
Okay.

17
00:02:23,949 --> 00:02:24,919
This way, please.

18
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:27,320
You're rushing in but you don't even have money.

19
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,320
Hold on.

20
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:30,030
I'll take you somewhere nice.

21
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:30,430
Let's go.

22
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,560
This place looks pretty good to me.

23
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,710
Come on, let's go.

24
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:35,000
Zhuifeng also wants to stay here.

25
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,750
Let's go.

26
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:36,750
I'm staying here.

27
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:40,120
As long as there's a bed,

28
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:39,530
[Jiqing Inn]

29
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,310
that's enough.

30
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:43,480
When I was on campaign,

31
00:02:43,510 --> 00:02:44,710
I even slept outdoors.

32
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:46,240
This is already good enough.

33
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,960
Sir,

34
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:48,470
two superior rooms.

35
00:02:48,470 --> 00:02:49,120
There are no rooms left.

36
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,650
Can't you see I'm sleeping?

37
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:52,630
Don't scrimp too much when traveling.

38
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,000
You can't save money to this extent.

39
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:54,710
Why don't we

40
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:56,260
stay at the first inn?

41
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:57,120
Wait.

42
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:00,360
I'll go find us rooms.

43
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,190
You stay here

44
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,250
and feed Zhuifeng.

45
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:03,079
Remember,

46
00:03:03,610 --> 00:03:04,940
feed it with good stuff.

47
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:08,820
Good stuff, okay?

48
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:13,520
She treats you

49
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:15,670
better than she treats herself.

50
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:16,840
Let's go.

51
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:19,080
Come on.

52
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:31,110
Place your bets! Place your bets!

53
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,450
Place your bets!

54
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:44,650
Big!

55
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:45,430
Big!

56
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:48,350
Four, five, six! Big!

57
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:53,770
Small!

58
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,000
This money

59
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:58,090
should be enough.

60
00:03:59,079 --> 00:03:59,710
Bro,

61
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,690
how about a couple more rounds?

62
00:04:01,790 --> 00:04:02,870
Don't go, bro.

63
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:04,610
Play a couple more rounds!

64
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,280
Don't go!

65
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,740
Play a couple more rounds!

66
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:15,340
Stop!

67
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,120
Fruit is incredibly expensive this season,

68
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,630
and you're feeding it to a horse?

69
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,310
It's fine.

70
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,400
I have another basket here, saved just for you.

71
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,060
They're very sweet. Try some.

72
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,560
The rooms are ready too.

73
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,730
[The Premier Room]

74
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,269
Where did you get the money?

75
00:04:33,269 --> 00:04:34,470
I didn't steal or rob.

76
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,200
Going to bed so early?

77
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:08,320
Are you thirsty?

78
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:09,720
Is it early?

79
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:14,950
I don't feel very sleepy.

80
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:16,150
I'll go out for a walk.

81
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:19,830
Stop.

82
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:24,760
We've already gone through half the city,

83
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,690
and there really are no rooms left.

84
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,870
Tonight,

85
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,260
just relax and get some sleep.

86
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:35,210
I've seen everything.

87
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:42,710
Seems like it.

88
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,840
Are you not used to this bed?

89
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:05,920
No.

90
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,530
This bed is quite comfortable.

91
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,800
I just miss home.

92
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,510
Home?

93
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,310
You've only been there a few days and already call it home?

94
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,710
A crow in a magpie's nest.

95
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,480
My identity is unknown.

96
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,720
I still don't know who I am.

97
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,720
But I was fortunate enough to meet you,

98
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,390
who gave me a place to stay.

99
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,390
So the General's Residence

100
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:37,110
naturally feels like home to me.

101
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,360
In comparison,

102
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:43,160
you live each day so plainly,

103
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:46,200
even more like someone without a home.

104
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:52,130
When I was in Yunjing,

105
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:54,960
I had to be cautious about everything.

106
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:57,130
At 12,

107
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:59,610
I went to the battlefield with my father.

108
00:07:00,430 --> 00:07:01,830
In my memory,

109
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:04,000
it was only endless war.

110
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,390
I barely remember

111
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,120
the feeling of home.

112
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:16,940
But in this world, apart from the fires of the battlefield,

113
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,200
there are also hearth fires of ordinary homes.

114
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,720
Now that we're in Ninglan,

115
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,650
where resources are abundant,

116
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,720
how about

117
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,190
I add some furnishings

118
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,310
to your bedroom?

119
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,720
It would at least make it a bit warmer,

120
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,180
much better than how cold and empty it is now.

121
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:39,000
No.

122
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,480
It's just a place to sleep.

123
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:44,040
You can't see anything once you're asleep anyway.

124
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,300
It's a waste of effort.

125
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:49,480
Precisely because it's a place to sleep,

126
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,830
it should be warmer.

127
00:07:51,659 --> 00:07:52,830
You're a general,

128
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:55,070
fighting on the battlefield every day,

129
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:56,400
defending the country,

130
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,510
and carrying burdens no ordinary person could bear.

131
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,710
When you return home,

132
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,120
you deserve a proper,

133
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,680
warm place to rest.

134
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,040
Are you lecturing me?

135
00:08:09,310 --> 00:08:10,640
Rather than lecturing,

136
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,190
it's more of a hope.

137
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,830
Before I lost my memory,

138
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:21,800
I must have had many

139
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,030
close friends

140
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:24,550
and family.

141
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,430
But now,

142
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,040
you are the only person

143
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:33,310
in this world truly connected to me.

144
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:37,200
I want you to live well.

145
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:44,510
Alright.

146
00:08:45,430 --> 00:08:47,360
Since you're the teacher,

147
00:08:47,549 --> 00:08:49,080
you make the arrangements.

148
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,120
But,

149
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:52,240
you must never…

150
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,440
I won't gamble again.

151
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:03,130
[Yuxing Woodenware]

152
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:04,510
Three Double-Flower Crescent Stools,

153
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,790
a set of wooden screens,

154
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,760
Two curved-edge tables,

155
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:11,340
four carved crescent stools.

156
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,410
Keep the change.

157
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,610
Thank you, sir.

158
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,790
I'll arrange people

159
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:19,930
to deliver your purchases right now.

160
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,650
You spend money lavishly.

161
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,570
You lead troops in battles all year round,

162
00:09:27,570 --> 00:09:29,420
risking your life.

163
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:30,810
Using some nice things

164
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,670
is only what you deserve.

165
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,730
As for the rest of the money,

166
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:38,150
after we return to Lucity,

167
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:39,950
donate it to those in need for me.

168
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:43,310
It's ill-gotten money anyway.

169
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,120
You're actually using it to earn a good reputation.

170
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,780
Gambling should be punished.

171
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,960
I was just

172
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:49,200
acting on justice,

173
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,220
and at the same time did a bit of good for them,

174
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:53,150
helping them earn some good karma.

175
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,240
When I saw this plain jade hairpin just now,

176
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,100
I immediately took a liking to it.

177
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:05,120
I think it suits you perfectly.

178
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,300
It's for...

179
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:08,630
It's for me?

180
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,780
You're always in a military uniform.

181
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,660
I think

182
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,400
only this plain jade hairpin

183
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:15,090
wouldn't look awkward on you.

184
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,280
You don't like it?

185
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:26,350
It's ugly.

186
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,550
It's not ugly.

187
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,200
You're beautiful anyway.

188
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:09,990
Don't take it off.

189
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,260
This is the first time I've given someone a gift.

190
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:20,040
Thanks for indulging me.

191
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:38,560
[Jing'an Bookstore]

192
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:44,250
Why did you stop?

193
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,880
Don't you like biographies?

194
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,310
A bookstore this big

195
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,000
must have everything.

196
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,510
If you find the ones you like,

197
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:54,470
you won't have to trouble Su Muyang

198
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:55,750
to search everywhere.

199
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,240
I noticed that you didn't even touch the biographies

200
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,440
he gave you last time.

201
00:12:00,770 --> 00:12:02,320
Whether he really betrayed you

202
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:02,910
or

203
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:05,170
was genuinely forced by circumstances,

204
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:06,260
I guess now

205
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:08,270
you just don't want anything

206
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,030
to do with him.

207
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:12,550
It's not that.

208
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,200
Really.

209
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,720
I just...

210
00:12:16,150 --> 00:12:18,010
don't like biographies anymore.

211
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:21,990
I thought if I bought more biographies,

212
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:23,910
you could forget the past

213
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:25,200
and enjoy reading.

214
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,610
But since you don't like them anymore,

215
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,410
just forget it.

216
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,050
It's really a shame.

217
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,720
This bookstore is huge—

218
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,910
there might be many rare editions.

219
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:40,000
I have a collection of military books

220
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,980
I've been collecting for years,

221
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,690
but I'm still missing one volume.

222
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,020
They might have it here.

